On 8/28/13 3:23 PM, Adrian Farrel wrote:
> Thanks for the heads-up, Brian.
>
> I think that replacing the reference to the draft with a statement that the
> definition is produced in another WG might not be good enough.
> How will this WG know what to work on until LWIG have defined the concepts?

The key work is extending the 6LoWPAN RFCs to other link layers.  The 
LWIG definition offers a baseline for where those RFCs may be 
applicable.  One option thrown around on the mailing list was to add the 
definitions to the charter rather than rely on the LWIG document (which 
is no longer mentioned in the charter).

>
> Maybe, however, the issue is that you are trying to split 6lo work from 6man
> work using a line that is hard to draw. How constrained does a node have to be
> before the work moves from 6man to 6lo?

The line is quite clear to me and it is drawn based on where the 6LoWPAN 
RFCs  are applicable.

Regards,
Brian

