Hi All,

There have been a lot of discussion in the list and I am catching up with t=
hem.

Here are some proposed text for the charter and some thoughts ( as per the =
following email  from Brian ) .

CURRENT


 6Lo focuses on Internet Area work that is needed for constrained node
networks, as the term is defined by the LWIG working group.=20

NEW:

6Lo focuses on Internet Area work that is needed for constrained node Netwo=
rks. The constrained node networks have  limited functionality compared to =
the  common IP networks composed of line-powered and high-capacity devices.=
 An example of constrained networks is IPv6 over IEEE 802.15.4(6LoWPAN).
The constrained nodes can be characterized by many different categories suc=
h as node capability, cost of networks, media constraints, regulatory limit=
s, bit-rates etc.=20


CURRENT
6Lo works on small, focused pieces of Internet Area work. 6Lo does not take=
 on
larger cross-layer efforts. The working group will continue to reuse existi=
ng
protocols and mechanisms whenever reasonable and possible.

QUESTION:  Would like to know what we mean by "small focused pieces of Inte=
rnet Area work" ?

Would it be better to say "6Lo will work on focused pieces of Internet Area=
 for which the work already started=20
on the IPv6-over-foo and provide generic guidelines for IPv6 running on con=
strained link-layers".

Will this group develop any work on provisioning of the constrained nodes? =
Gateway devices between Internet (IPv6) and  constrained networks?
If so,  it would be good to clarify them.

CURRENT:
Security and management work that is not specific to the link layers being
worked on is out of scope.

QUESTION: Is it trying to say?

Any new security and management work that is not specific to the constraine=
d link, is out of scope.
This sentence is not clear to me.


The rest looks fine to me.

Thanks,
-Samita







